                  <persName id="t18230910-303-person2620">
                  JOHN 
                  PARTRIDGE
               <interp inst="t18230910-303-person2620" type="surname" value="PARTRIDGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-303-person2620" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-303-person2620" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am beadle of Whitechapel. On the 25th of August I was in Rosemary-lane, and saw the prisoner offering three spoons for sale to a Jew. I asked him where he got them from. He said from Mrs. Noon, of Ailiff-street. I took him in custody with them, and found out the prosecutrix.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. WALFORD. Q. He was not sober, was he - A. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-303-person2621">
                  MARY 
                  EDBURY
               <interp inst="t18230910-303-person2621" type="surname" value="EDBURY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-303-person2621" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-303-person2621" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of 
               <persName id="t18230910-303-person2622">
                  John 
                  Edbury
               <interp inst="t18230910-303-person2622" type="surname" value="Edbury"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-303-person2622" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-303-person2622" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and live in <placeName id="t18230910-303-crimeloc1629">Little Aliff-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-303-crimeloc1629" type="placeName" value="Little Aliff-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-303-crimeloc1629" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-303-off1627 t18230910-303-crimeloc1629"></join>. The prisoner was recommended to me as a lodger, and was one night in my house. I did not miss the spoons until they were brought to me. They were taken off the back-room table. He was at my house a quarter of an hour before.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. He might have taken them in a joke - A. Very likely.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. She sent me out for rum, and I do not know whether they were put into my pocket or not, for I never saw them.</p>
